    <stitle>ALTERNATOR: DELCO-REMY 26-SI SERIES - REPAIR PROCEDURES - BEARING REPLACEMENT AND LUBRICATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="2">
        <title>BEARING REPLACEMENT AND LUBRICATION</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The bearings normally will operate between engine overhaul periods without attention. The drive end
                bearing is a permanently sealed lubricated bearing. At time of engine overhaul, the bearings and seals
                should be replaced, and a fresh supply of lubricant added to the rectifier-end bearing reservoir.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Rectifier End Frame Bearing Replacement</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove cover plate (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0801805">Item 1, Figure 10</hotlnk>) from rectifier end frame cover (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0801805">Item 5, Figure 10</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801810">Figure 9</hotlnk>for all Item number callouts in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801810" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801809" filename="../figg08/G0801809.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Rectifier End Frame Bearing Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>A. .145-.150" (3.68-3.81 MM)</callout1>
                    <callout1>B. .640-.650" (16.25-16.51 MM)</callout1>
                    <callout1>1. GREASE RESERVOIR</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SHAFT</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. PLUG</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. INNER RACE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. BEARING</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. SEAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. END FRAME</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">From inside the rectifier-end frame, press plug (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0801810">Item 3, Figure 9</hotlnk>), bearing (Item 5) with seal out of rectifier
                    end frame.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Pull inner race (Item 4) off rotor shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press new inner race onto shaft to dimension "A" in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0801810">Figure 9</hotlnk>
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press new bearing (with seal) (Items 5 and 6) into end frame bearing housing. Press into
                    frame from the seal end of the bearing to dimension "B" in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0801810">Figure 9</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Fill grease reservoir (Item 1) three quarters full of high temperature lubricant.
                    Arrange the lubricant so a portion of it will contact the bearing after assembly. Refer to GROUP 10,
                    LUBRICATION for the proper lubricant.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press new plug (Item 3) into end frame until it is flush with the outer edge of the
                    bearing housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Drive End Bearing Replacement</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0801805">Figure 10</hotlnk>for all Item number callouts in parentheses.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0801805" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0801810" filename="../figg08/G0801810.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Alternator Exploded View</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SCREW AND LOCKWASHER - RECTIFIER PLATE COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RECTIFIER PLATE COVER</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. SCREW AND LOCKWASHER - RECTIFIER PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SCREW AND LOCKWASHER - RECTIFIER PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. RECTIFIER PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. GASKET - RECTIFIER END</callout1>
                    <callout1>7. SCREW AND LOCKWASHER - ATTACH DIODE HEAT SINK</callout1>
                    <callout1>8. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>9. INSULATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>10. LEAD - REGULATOR STUD TO DIODE HEAT SINK</callout1>
                    <callout1>11. DIODE HEAT SINK</callout1>
                    <callout1>12. DIODE</callout1>
                    <callout1>13. STUD PACKAGE</callout1>
                    <callout1>14. HEAT SINK ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>15. INSULATION - BETWEEN DIODE HEAT SINK AND REGULATOR HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>16. SCREW AND LOCKWASHER - ATTACH DIODE HEAT SINK</callout1>
                    <callout1>17. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>18. INSULATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>19. OUTPUT TERMINAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>20. TERMINAL PACKAGE - OUTPUT</callout1>
                    <callout1>21. RECTIFIER END FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>22. BUSHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>23. BEARING - RECTIFIER END OUTER RACE</callout1>
                    <callout1>24. BEARING - RECTIFIER END INNER RACE</callout1>
                    <callout1>25. PIPE PLUG</callout1>
                    <callout1>26. CAP - "R" TERMINAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>27. TERMINAL PACKAGE - "R" TERMINAL</callout1>
                    <callout1>28. SCREW - GROUND</callout1>
                    <callout1>29. LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>30. SUPPORT - REGULATOR GROUND LEAD</callout1>
                    <callout1>31. PLUG - RECTIFIER END HOUSING</callout1>
                    <callout1>32. NUT - DIODE TRIO LEAD TO STATOR LEAD ATTACHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>33. DIODE TRIO ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>34. WASHER - DIODE TRIO TO CAPACITOR ATTACHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>35. SCREW AND LOCKWASHER - DIODE TRIO TO CAPACITOR ATTACHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>36. PLATE - REGULATOR MOUNTING</callout1>
                    <callout1>37. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>38. SCREW AND LOCKWASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>39. REGULATOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>40. SCREW AND LOCKWASHER - INSULATED</callout1>
                    <callout1>41. SCREW AND LOCKWASHER - INSULATED</callout1>
                    <callout1>42. NUT REGULATOR STUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>43. CLIP - TERMINAL - STATOR LEADS</callout1>
                    <callout1>44. INSULATION BETWEEN</callout1>
                    <callout1>45. STATOR ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                    <callout1>46. SCREW - FIELD COIL AND SUPPORT ATTACHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>47. FIELD COIL AND SUPPORT</callout1>
                    <callout1>48. ROTOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>49. RETAINER PLATE</callout1>
                    <callout1>50. COLLAR</callout1>
                    <callout1>51. BEARING</callout1>
                    <callout1>52. DRIVE END FRAME</callout1>
                    <callout1>53. SCREW - RETAINER PLATE ATTACHING</callout1>
                    <callout1>54. SLINGER</callout1>
                    <callout1>55. THRU BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>56. FAN</callout1>
                    <callout1>57. BAFFLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>58. PULLEY</callout1>
                    <callout1>59. WASHER</callout1>
                    <callout1>60. NUT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove shaft nut (Item 60,
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0801805">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove washer (Item 59), pulley (Item 58), baffle (Item 57), fan (Item 56) and slinger
                    (Item 54) from shaft.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove through bolts (Item 55) that fasten the drive end frame and rectifier end frame
                    together.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Separate the drive end frame (Item 52) and rotor (Item 48) from the rectifier end frame
                    (Item 21).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 4 screws (Item 53) that fasten the retainer plate (Item 49) to the drive end
                    frame.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove rotor (Item 48) with retainer plate (Item 49), collar (Item 50), and sealed
                    bearing (Item 51) from the drive end frame.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support the bearing (Item 51) by the inner race and press it off the rotor shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the collar (Item 50) and retainer plate (Item 49) from rotor shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace seals in retainer plate and drive end frame. The seals must be installed so the
                    lip is toward or next to the bearing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position retainer plate (Item 49) (with gasket) on rotor shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install collar (Item 50) on rotor shaft.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press the sealed bearing (Item 51) on rotor shaft.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <important>
                        <para>Press only on inner race to install new bearing on rotor shaft against the collar (Item
                            50).
                        </para>
                    </important>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position sealed bearing (Item 51), gasket and retainer plate (Item 49) in drive end
                    frame. Secure retainer plate with 4 screws (Item 53) through the drive end frame (Item 52). Tighten
                    until snug.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
